  "text": "The structure of the paper is as follows. In Section 2 we provide necessary background including the outline of quaternionic Feix-Kaledin construction [CITATION_1] . In Section 3 we give conditions on the data in quaternionic Feix-Kaledin construction which are necessary to obtain as a result a quaternion-Kähler manifold with a rotation S 1 -isometry and in Section 4 we prove that this continuous are sufficient. In Section 5 we discuss the case when S is compact, proving in particular that the quaternion-Kähler on a neighbourhood of S is fully encoded in the Kähler metric on S and the contact line bundle restricted to S on the twistor space. We finish in Section 6 by discussing examples and relation with the hyperkähler/quaternion-Kähler correspondence.",
